---

## REVIEW CHECKLISTS

### 1. Architecture Alignment
- [ ] File in correct folder `server/src/modules/<name>/`
- [ ] Dot-separated naming: `<name>.model.js`, `<name>.controller.js`
- [ ] Controller: HTTP only — no DB logic, no business logic
- [ ] Service: all business logic — no `req`/`res`
- [ ] Routes: only wire middleware + controller — no inline logic
- [ ] Model: schema + associations only — no query logic
- [ ] Validation schema in `<name>.validation.js`, not inline

## 2. Database / Model Alignment
- [ ] Every column matches DATABASE.md (name, type, constraints)
- [ ] `paranoid: true` on models with `deleted_at` (Product, User)
- [ ] `timestamps: true` on all models
- [ ] UUID PKs: `type: DataTypes.UUID, defaultValue: DataTypes.UUIDV4`
- [ ] DECIMAL columns use `DataTypes.DECIMAL(10, 2)` — never FLOAT
- [ ] Associations in `associate(models)` static method
- [ ] `ON DELETE` behaviors match schema (CASCADE vs SET NULL)
- [ ] No raw quantity updates — inventory uses atomic operations only

### 3. API Contract Alignment
- [ ] Route path matches exactly (e.g. `/api/products/:slug` not `:id`)
- [ ] HTTP method matches API.md
- [ ] `authenticate` middleware on all protected routes
- [ ] `authorize('admin')` on admin-only routes
- [ ] Feature gate applied where required (wishlist, reviews, coupons)
- [ ] Response shape: `{ success, data, message, meta }`
- [ ] Error shape: `{ success: false, error: { code, message, details } }`
- [ ] Correct HTTP status codes (201 create, 409 conflict, 422 validation)
- [ ] Pagination on all list endpoints

### 4. Security Checklist
- [ ] Rate limiting: auth routes use specific limiters, not global
- [ ] Input validation: every user-facing route has Joi schema
- [ ] Sanitization: HTML → `sanitizeRichText()`, plain → `sanitizePlainText()
- [ ] JWT: always use `authenticate`` middleware, never check token manually
- [ ] Password: NEVER returned in any response
- [ ] File upload: MIME via `file-type` package, not extension; SVG rejected
- [ ] Inventory: `Sequelize.literal()` atomic updates only — never read-modify-write
- [ ] Payment idempotency: use `orderId` as idempotency key
- [ ] Stripe webhooks: verify signature before processing
- [ ] Slugs: use `generateUniqueSlug()` utility — never manual
- [ ] No raw SQL — all DB access through Sequelize ORM
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets — all from `process.env`

### 5. Edge Cases Checklist
- [ ] Soft delete: queries use `paranoid` or `where: { deletedAt: null }`
- [ ] Cart price drift: checkout re-fetches prices from DB — never trusts cache
- [ ] Price conflict: 409 `PRICE_CHANGED` with old/new diff
- [ ] Stock conflict: 409 `INSUFFICIENT_STOCK`
- [ ] Coupon validation: all 7 rules checked in transaction
- [ ] OrderItem snapshots: `snapshotName`, `snapshotPrice`, `snapshotImage`, `snapshotSku`
- [ ] Address snapshot: `Order.shippingAddressSnapshot` is JSONB copy at purchase time
- [ ] Guest cart merge: `POST /cart/merge` triggered on login
- [ ] Deleted products in cart: filtered out with user warning
- [ ] Feature gate: toggleable routes check `features.<name>` setting

---

## CODE PATTERNS — ALWAYS USE THESE

### Response helper (never use res.json() directly)
```javascript
const { success, error, paginated } = require('../../utils/response');

return success(res, data, 'Product created', 201);
return error(res, 'VALIDATION_ERROR', 'Invalid input', 400, details);
return paginated(res, rows, { page, limit, total });
```

### Controller shape
```javascript
const create = async (req, res, next) => {
  try {
    const data = await ProductService.create(req.body, req.user.id);
    return success(res, data, 'Product created', 201);
  } catch (err) {
    next(err); // always pass to error handler — never catch silently
  }
};
```

### Service shape
```javascript
const create = async (payload, actingUserId) => {
  return sequelize.transaction(async (t) => {
    const product = await Product.create(payload, { transaction: t });
    await AuditService.log({
      userId: actingUserId, action: 'CREATE',
      entity: 'Product', entityId: product.id
    }, t);
    return product;
  });
};
```

### Atomic inventory reservation (CRITICAL — never deviate)
```javascript
// CORRECT
const [affected] = await Product.update(
  { reservedQty: Sequelize.literal(`reserved_qty + ${qty}`) },
  {
    where: {
      id: productId,
      [Op.and]: Sequelize.literal(`(quantity - reserved_qty) >= ${qty}`)
    },
    transaction: t
  }
);
if (affected === 0) throw new AppError('INSUFFICIENT_STOCK', 409);

// WRONG — race condition, never do this
const product = await Product.findByPk(productId);
product.reservedQty += qty;
await product.save();
```

### Feature gate
```javascript
router.post('/wishlist/items',
  authenticate,
  featureGate('wishlist'),
  wishlistController.add
);
```

### Slug generation
```javascript
const { generateUniqueSlug } = require('../../utils/slugify');
const slug = await generateUniqueSlug(name, Product);
```

---

## NAMING STANDARDS

| Item         | Rule                  | Example                  |
|--------------|-----------------------|--------------------------|
| API routes   | kebab-case, plural    | `/api/order-items`       |
| DB tables    | snake_case, plural    | `order_items`            |
| DB columns   | snake_case            | `first_name`             |
| Model fields | camelCase             | `firstName`              |
| File names   | dot-separated         | `product.model.js`       |
| Functions    | camelCase verbs       | `createProduct`          |
| Constants    | UPPER_SNAKE           | `ORDER_STATUS`           |
| Error codes  | UPPER_SNAKE string    | `'INSUFFICIENT_STOCK'`   |
| Module dir   | singular lowercase    | `modules/product/`       |

---

## ORDER LIFECYCLE — NEVER DEVIATE

```
pending_payment → paid → processing → shipped → delivered
                                             ↘ cancelled
paid → refunded
```

Status transitions made ONLY by:
- Stripe webhook: `payment_intent.succeeded` → `paid`
- Admin: `PUT /orders/:id/status`
- Customer cancel: `POST /orders/:id/cancel` (only if `pending_payment`)

---

## KNOWN GAPS — FLAG PROACTIVELY

When code touches these areas, always flag the gap to the user:

- `media` table missing — Media model doesn't exist in DB yet
- `password_reset_tokens` table missing — create before forgot-password flow
- `email_verification_tokens` table missing — create before email verify flow
- `product_variants` no soft delete — variants hard-delete when product deleted; warn if referenced in cart
- `reviews` no `order_id` FK — verified purchase check requires manual order query

---

## SLASH COMMANDS

- `/scaffold <module>` — Generate full module skeleton (all 5 files)
- `/review <file>` — Run all 5 checklists against provided code
- `/debug <error>` — Systematic root cause analysis

---

## OUTPUT FORMAT

Always structure output as:

```
## Plan
[2–3 sentences: what you're doing and why]

## Files
[one code block per file, full path as label]

## Notes
[migrations to run, env vars needed, known gaps, follow-up tasks]
```

Never output partial files. If a file is too long, say so and ask which section to prioritize.

