# SKILL: Performance & Optimization
# Applies to: client/src/**, server/src/**

## Frontend Performance Rules

### Code splitting — always lazy load pages
```javascript
// client/src/router.jsx — lazy load every page
import { lazy, Suspense } from 'react';
const ProductListPage = lazy(() => import('./pages/customer/ProductListPage'));
const CheckoutPage    = lazy(() => import('./pages/customer/CheckoutPage'));

// Wrap routes in Suspense
<Suspense fallback={<PageLoader />}>
  <Route path="/products" element={<ProductListPage />} />
</Suspense>
```

### Memoization — use only when you have a proven re-render problem
```javascript
// useMemo for expensive derived values
const sortedProducts = useMemo(
  () => [...products].sort((a, b) => a.price - b.price),
  [products]
);

// useCallback for stable function refs passed to memoized children
const handleAddToCart = useCallback((id) => dispatch(addItem(id)), [dispatch]);

// React.memo for pure list items that re-render frequently
export const ProductCard = React.memo(function ProductCard({ product, onAdd }) {
  ...
});
```

### Image optimization
```jsx
// Always specify width/height to prevent layout shift
// Use loading="lazy" for below-the-fold images
<img
  src={product.image}
  alt={product.name}
  width={400}
  height={400}
  loading="lazy"
  style={{ objectFit: 'cover' }}
/>
```

### List virtualization — required for lists > 100 items
```jsx
// Use react-window for large lists (product catalog, order history)
import { FixedSizeGrid } from 'react-window';

<FixedSizeGrid
  columnCount={3}
  columnWidth={300}
  rowCount={Math.ceil(products.length / 3)}
  rowHeight={400}
  width={900}
  height={600}
>
  {({ rowIndex, columnIndex, style }) => (
    <div style={style}>
      <ProductCard product={products[rowIndex * 3 + columnIndex]} />
    </div>
  )}
</FixedSizeGrid>
```

## Backend Performance Rules

### Database query optimization
```javascript
// ALWAYS specify attributes — never fetch * in production
const products = await Product.findAll({
  attributes: ['id', 'name', 'price', 'salePrice', 'slug'],  // explicit
  include: [{
    model: ProductImage,
    attributes: ['url', 'isPrimary'],
    where: { isPrimary: true },
    required: false,
  }],
  limit,
  offset,
});

// NEVER do N+1 — always eager load associations
// WRONG
const orders = await Order.findAll();
for (const order of orders) {
  order.items = await OrderItem.findAll({ where: { orderId: order.id } }); // N+1!
}

// CORRECT
const orders = await Order.findAll({
  include: [{ model: OrderItem, include: [Product] }]
});
```

### Pagination — required on every list endpoint
```javascript
// Always paginate — never return unbounded lists
const page  = parseInt(req.query.page)  || 1;
const limit = Math.min(parseInt(req.query.limit) || 20, 100); // cap at 100
const offset = (page - 1) * limit;

const { count, rows } = await Product.findAndCountAll({ limit, offset });
return paginated(res, rows, { page, limit, total: count });
```

### Caching with Redis — apply to expensive reads
```javascript
// Cache pattern: check cache → miss → query DB → set cache
const cacheKey = `products:list:${JSON.stringify(params)}`;
const cached = await redis.get(cacheKey);
if (cached) return success(res, JSON.parse(cached));

const data = await ProductService.getAll(params);
await redis.setEx(cacheKey, 300, JSON.stringify(data)); // 5 min TTL
return success(res, data);
```

### Response compression — must be enabled in Express
```javascript
// server/src/app.js — ensure this is present
const compression = require('compression');
app.use(compression()); // gzip all responses
```

## Performance Checklist
- [ ] All pages lazy loaded with `React.lazy()` + `Suspense`
- [ ] `React.memo` / `useMemo` / `useCallback` used only for proven bottlenecks
- [ ] Images have `width`, `height`, and `loading="lazy"` for below-fold
- [ ] Lists > 100 items use `react-window` virtualization
- [ ] DB queries specify explicit `attributes` — no `SELECT *`
- [ ] No N+1 queries — associations are eager loaded
- [ ] All list endpoints paginated with max 100 cap
- [ ] Expensive reads cached in Redis with appropriate TTL
- [ ] `compression` middleware enabled in Express
- [ ] `staleTime` tuned per query volatility in React Query
